===Etymology===
From Greek '''[[pater]]''', ''father'', + '''[[onomatos]]''', ''name''

===Noun===
'''patronymic''', plural '''[[patronymics]]'''

# name acquired from one's father's first name.  Some cultures use a patronymic where other cultures use a [[surname]] or family name; other cultures (e.g., Russia) use both a patronymic and a surname.

====Usage Note====
A patronymic is often formed by adding a prefix or suffix to a name.

